    <title type="text">MesoCalc</title>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<a href="http://baptiste.meles.free.fr/site/mesocalc.html">MesoCalc: a
      Mesopotamian Calculator</a><br /><a
      href="http://draft.blogger.com/blogger.g?blogID=116259103207720939" name="whatis">
      </a><br /><blockquote class="tr_bq"><a
      href="http://draft.blogger.com/blogger.g?blogID=116259103207720939" name="whatis"> <span
      style="font-size: x-small;">MesoCalc is a Mesopotamian calculator.</span><br
      /><span style="font-size: x-small;">
      </span></a></blockquote><blockquote><span style="font-size:
      x-small;"><a href="http://draft.blogger.com/blogger.g?blogID=116259103207720939"
      name="whatis"> People interested in Mesopotamian mathematics can use it to compute with
      integers in sexagesimal place-value notation. See the </a><a
      href="http://baptiste.meles.free.fr/site/mesocalc.html#note">note about the sexagesimal
      place-value notation</a> (SPVN) and the <a
      href="http://baptiste.meles.free.fr/site/mesocalc.html#biblio">bibliography</a>
      below.</span> </blockquote><blockquote> <span style="font-size:
      x-small;"> The present webpage <em>is</em> the program itself. Its latest
      version can be found on the official <a
      href="http://baptiste.meles.free.fr/site/mesocalc.html">MesoCalc page</a>. You are
      free to download this page, use it offline on your own computer or smartphone, modify the
      source code, and even redistribute your modifications under the terms of the GNU General Public
      License (see the <a
      href="http://baptiste.meles.free.fr/site/mesocalc.html#license">license</a>
      below).</span> </blockquote><blockquote> <span style="font-size:
      x-small;">This program was written in 2013 by <a
      href="http://baptiste.meles.free.fr/">Baptiste MÉLÈS</a> (Archives Henri Poincaré,
      Université de Lorraine) with the scientific assistance of Christine PROUST (CNRS, Université
      Paris-Diderot) in the framework of the <a href="http://sawerc.hypotheses.org/">SAW
      Project</a> (Mathematical Sciences in the Ancient World), headed by Karine Chemla (CNRS,
      Université Paris-Diderot).</span> </blockquote><blockquote> <span
      style="font-size: x-small;">If you see bugs or want new features, please <a
      href="mailto:baptiste.meles@normalesup.org">contact Baptiste Mélès</a>.
      </span></blockquote><blockquote class="tr_bq"><span style="font-size:
      x-small;"><a href="http://draft.blogger.com/blogger.g?blogID=116259103207720939"
      name="operations"> </a></span><br /><span style="font-size:
      x-small;"><a href="http://draft.blogger.com/blogger.g?blogID=116259103207720939"
      name="operations">Available operations:</a></span><br /><span
      style="font-size: x-small;"><a
      href="http://draft.blogger.com/blogger.g?blogID=116259103207720939" name="operations">
      </a></span><br /><ul><span style="font-size: x-small;"><a
      href="http://draft.blogger.com/blogger.g?blogID=116259103207720939" name="operations">
      </a></span><li><span style="font-size: x-small;"><a
      href="http://draft.blogger.com/blogger.g?blogID=116259103207720939" name="operations">
      </a><a
      href="http://baptiste.meles.free.fr/site/mesocalc.html#conversions">Conversions</a>:
      from decimal to sexagesimal, from sexagesimal to decimal; </span></li><li>
      <span style="font-size: x-small;"><a
      href="http://baptiste.meles.free.fr/site/mesocalc.html#properties">Number
      properties</a>: regularity, prime factors; </span></li><li> <span
      style="font-size: x-small;"><a
      href="http://baptiste.meles.free.fr/site/mesocalc.html#addition">Addition</a>:
      addition, substraction; </span></li><li> <span style="font-size:
      x-small;"><a
      href="http://baptiste.meles.free.fr/site/mesocalc.html#multiplication">Multiplication</a>:
      multiplication, reciprocal, quotient, rule of three; </span></li><li>
      <span style="font-size: x-small;"><a
      href="http://baptiste.meles.free.fr/site/mesocalc.html#powers">Powers and roots</a>:
      square, square root, cube, cube root; </span></li><li> <span
      style="font-size: x-small;"><a
      href="http://baptiste.meles.free.fr/site/mesocalc.html#tables">Tables</a>:
      multiplication tables, table of reciprocals, list of regular numbers, list of reciprocal
      numbers; </span></li><li> <span style="font-size: x-small;"><a
      href="http://baptiste.meles.free.fr/site/mesocalc.html#units">Measuring units</a>: add
      lengths, compute brickage and carriage (<em>nalbalum</em> and
      <em>nazbalum</em>). </span></li></ul></blockquote><br
      />]]></content>
